SIMPLE: water_dog
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water dog
<hw>Wa"ter dog`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
dog accustomed to the water, or trained to retrieve waterfowl.
Retrievers, waters spaniels, and Newfoundland dogs are so
trained.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The menobranchus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A small floating cloud, supposed to indicate
rain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A sailor, esp. an old sailor; an old salt.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water drain</ent>⟦br⟧
